reams from the open mouth of the white bottle into a yellow bucket. The liquid catches the light as it flows in a clear, continuous pour. The Ajax bottle then stands on a square-tiled floor beside the yellow bucket. A mop with a yellow handle and gray mop head slides across the tiles, leaving a visibly wet, glossy path. The cleaned area reflects light more strongly than the duller surrounding tile. Bold red on-screen text appears across the lower part of the floor reading, “GOOD FOR NO-WAX FLOORS,” with the Ajax bottle and yellow bucket still positioned to the left.\n\nBack in the bright home setting, the man holds the white Ajax bottle close to his nose, sniffing the open top. He looks thoughtful and then lowers it slightly. Behind him, the woman in sunglasses appears near the French doors, smiling as she comes up behind his shoulder. He faces forward at first, then turns his head toward her. She stands close beside him, still smiling, and raises one hand to the edge of her sunglasses. With a playful expression, she tips the glasses down slightly so her eyes are just visible over the top, then looks toward him and forward again. He gives a small satisfied smile while she continues holding the sunglasses by one corner.\n\nThe two stand framed by the white doorway and leafy greenery outside. The man holds the Ajax bottle upright against his chest, label facing outward. The woman, still cheerful, brings in a clear rack or tray filled with colorful drinking glasses in yellow, green, and orange tones. She holds it up between them, smiling as if presenting a new use for the sunglasses or for the time saved. The man turns to look at the tray, still holding the Ajax bottle. She then carries the tray away toward the right, leaving him looking after her with the bottle in hand.\n\nThe final product display returns to the shiny pale floor in the yellow kitchen. The white Ajax jug stands prominently in the foreground, its red cap and bold “AJAX” label clearly visible, while the glossy floor stretches back toward the French doors. Large red slanted text appears above and beside the bottle reading, “THE SHINE SHINES THROUGH.” A small rectangular inset shows the smiling woman wearing her oversized dark sunglasses, reinforcing the image of the floor’s bright shine.",
